<subSubSection id="36AAFC461D06DEF247A2ACA58B0747C8" pageId="null" pageNumber="296" type="vernacular_names">
<paragraph id="4981DBD77F1B504DC1173BAC62F293B8" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">Kleines Labkraut</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</title>
<subSubSection id="4C68982133A7B03C604FDF3166361FDD" pageId="null" pageNumber="296" type="description">
<paragraph id="79A70C2378AAFD55EB4B1283A76BBD9C" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">
4-10 cm hoch, dichtrasig. Stengel aufrecht, fast immer kahl. Unterste 
<normalizedToken id="B5068B408D97AE4F959E868005453767" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
zur 
<normalizedToken id="8DEBB919B589D7AA7CA5E34241E1FF25" originalValue="Blütezeit" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">Bluetezeit</normalizedToken>
noch vorhanden. Mittlere 
<normalizedToken id="3CA20959B61EF65699720DE05C8A1B51" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
zu 7-9 im Quirl, 0,4-1,0 cm lang, 
<emphasis id="8BAEB728C6EBDCC7FDF5D9E0278BF551" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">10</emphasis>
- 
<emphasis id="115A9612AAC7BC299A29847FECF6ABE1" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">
15mal so lang wie breit, sehr schmal lanzettlich bis 
<normalizedToken id="B8E9B890D96A07A2D55655FAB66254A2" originalValue="nadelförmig" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">nadelfoermig</normalizedToken>
, steif, 
<normalizedToken id="5E188A983512FBE1FEA84B6275162818" originalValue="allmählich" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">allmaehlich</normalizedToken>
in die 0,5
</emphasis>
- 
<emphasis id="28D1A8CAC52BE95CF7B4B9C1D927EBBC" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">
0,9 mm lange hyaline Spitze 
<normalizedToken id="6A4C6F21543CFBF5829F71851F670DD4" originalValue="verschmälert" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">verschmaelert</normalizedToken>
, am Rande
</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="F7ECF4569C851F024D0C07867F46CF4B" originalValue="±" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">+/-</normalizedToken>
<emphasis id="639FE941E416C8D428008F172AF887B5" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">
flach, oft 
<normalizedToken id="FC9A9DEE864BED49DC5B3EED057E882C" originalValue="völlig" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">voellig</normalizedToken>
kahl und glatt. Mittelnerv
</emphasis>
⅓- 
<normalizedToken id="36994037EDF61307B2A730DF4B6861CA" originalValue="½" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">1/2</normalizedToken>
<emphasis id="F11B4218F0A18B561442AABF6C6E5CD8" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">so breit wie das Blatt</emphasis>
(bei den andern Arten im Gebiet fast immer weniger als ⅓ so breit). 
<normalizedToken id="1B38B80C50B418D9A33C24C73D37BDFF" originalValue="Blütenstände" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">Bluetenstaende</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="5BFD6A226967E581C55F906B79EA0F15" originalValue="wenigblütig" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">wenigbluetig</normalizedToken>
, kurz, mit von den obersten 1-2 Blattquirlen ausgehenden langen 
<normalizedToken id="BA7F44A3ACC6847FE64138844B64014F" originalValue="Seitenästen" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">Seitenaesten</normalizedToken>
, daher breit 
<normalizedToken id="BC04CF7AA93CE121A356F21E2228A6EC" originalValue="pyramidenförmig" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">pyramidenfoermig</normalizedToken>
. Krone 2-3 mm im Durchmesser, 
<normalizedToken id="11F855A6C16467C5AC5C3B68C367B2B8" originalValue="weiß" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">weiss</normalizedToken>
. 
<normalizedToken id="BC8870769E0F6A6061995488D5BF23DF" originalValue="Früchte" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">Fruechte</normalizedToken>
<emphasis id="7A26BC59A7C9BE4120CF5457947B44FD" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">
<normalizedToken id="774197748248D509C0D2B94291812D68" originalValue="±" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">+/-</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
glatt, ca. 1 mm hoch. - 
<normalizedToken id="74F4EC5399861F07F327FCDC973C041B" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">Bluete</normalizedToken>
: Sommer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="088C35654D83596422163ED7CD1E1BB9" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">
<emphasis id="290C18172EE386E3E91E326A3A9B9F94" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">Zytologische Angaben. 2n</emphasis>
= 
<emphasis id="FB2130BA0BE1B60E74B71772A5A6F1BE" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">22:</emphasis>
Material aus dem Val Queyras (Favarger 1969). 
<emphasis id="AF2CEA93425D6418EDB4AEB793250A70" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">2n</emphasis>
= 
<emphasis id="504389B4E8EC3FDB93DCC732E0D6216A" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">88:</emphasis>
Material von Marseille (Ehrendorfer 
<normalizedToken id="966BDE84E6344CA152743842099CAA0A" originalValue="unveröffentlicht" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">unveroeffentlicht</normalizedToken>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2958751AFB0CE8B868C4DB1DA63C3340" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">
<emphasis id="447274BF190A07F337F65BFC25E80C9E" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">Standort.</emphasis>
Montan und subalpin. Trockener, kalkhaltiger Ruhschutt (auch Gips), ohne geschlossene Vegetation, in warmen Lagen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5801CE521C96069466BA89BF0B36AA26" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">
<emphasis id="16A9CA56269BD54D52922114335AA09B" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">
Verbreitung. 
<normalizedToken id="59A281DE5F6BE34C35C6EE60CEB9BC76" originalValue="Südwestalpen-Pflanze" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">Suedwestalpen-Pflanze</normalizedToken>
:
</emphasis>
Von Montpellier und den Alpes Maritimes 
<normalizedToken id="69584FAFE1841781804587E5BB3D25BC" originalValue="nordwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">nordwaerts</normalizedToken>
bis zur Maurienne. - Im Gebiet: Maurienne (zwischen Modane und Bessans).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8358D13EE82C5E96A10BCFEFE1F1BB5C" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">
<emphasis id="E9BCA16F2327CF45E4C8E50C12CBD0DE" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">
Bemerkungen. 
<taxonomicName id="637191323DFF2AFB1DDC24839ABD416D" authority="Vill." authorityName="Vill." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Galium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="null" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hypnoides">G. hypnoides Vill.</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
(
<taxonomicName id="D814C45A3E938D0C80E669A079645BA3" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Galium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="null" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="pusillum" subSpecies="hypnoides">
<emphasis id="9D46C3665BEE6ECC8084C284ACEF818C" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">G. pusillum</emphasis>
ssp. 
<emphasis id="1E9945045396C35E79F7698C842178D2" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">hypnoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[Vill.] Ehrend.) ist eine besondere, nahe verwandte Sippe, die nur am Mont Ventoux vorkommt. Die im Gebiet vorkommenden Pflanzen 
<normalizedToken id="C4972C8010D8D219B3C4F07E47704F0B" originalValue="müssen" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">muessen</normalizedToken>
der Sippe 
<taxonomicName id="6272FC79AECAA2B586993113D3C06681" authority="Vill." authorityName="Vill." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Galium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="null" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jussiei">
<emphasis id="FD5AC78C7AF042BA87FFC48EF22CB815" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">G. Jussiei</emphasis>
Vill.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="739A7ABBA3CEE7DE359E7A6F51DA96F9" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Galium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="null" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pusillum">
<emphasis id="64F037D7ABD8F749EF25847B09D94B5E" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">G. pusillum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ssp. 
<taxonomicName id="C0B7582A8E8045E20421D49F7274A96B" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Galium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="null" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jussiei">
<emphasis id="89E49A24C24E7A303A437770F68F620B" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="296">Jussiei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[Vill.] Ehrendorfer inedit.) zugeordnet werden, die von den Alpes Maritimes bis Savoyen verbreitet ist.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
